NAME
    applwrit - sends a message to a GEM application.

SYNOPSIS
    applwrit <GEMAPP> <MSG> [ARGS...] 

    <GEMAPP> name of GEM application targetted. This name must
             respect the GEM convention (max 8 chars without 
             filename extension).
    <MSG>    message number (integer value).
    <ARGS>   possible arguments 
    
DESCRIPTION
    This command sends a message to a GEM application using the
    GEM pipe. It is just an interface to the appl_write AES 
    function. <MSG> parameter matches to word 0 in the AES message
    buffer and <ARGS> parameters matche to word 3-7 in the AES
    message buffer. The rule is (see EXAMPLES):

       one integer value - one word
       one string value - two words
    
    This command could be very usefull to communicate with 
    applications supporting usual GEM protocol as AV-protocol
    or GEMscript protocol.
    
    applfind command can be used to know is an GEM application is
    loaded in memory and ready to receive a message.


EXAMPLES
    request 'QED' to open a document
    % applwrite QED 18193 file.txt
    
    request desktop to open a document
    % applwrite $AVSERVER image.gif

SEE ALSO
    applfind, vastart, avserver, open.


